re, or scaling the seriousness of a crime.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aScaling (Social sciences) 0aScaling (Social sciences). 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / General.2bisacsh  aacademic.  aanalysis.  acommunication.  acrime.  aethnographic.  aethnography.  aglobal.  alabor.  alarge.  alocal.  aluminos.  amacro.  amacroevents.  amethodology.  amicro.  amicroevents.  aopposites.  apractical application.  apractical labor.  aproduct.  ascale.  ascales.  ascaling.  ascholarly.  ascientific study.  asmall.  asocial life.  asocial science.  asocial studies.1 aBauman, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarr, E. Summerson, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFisher, Brooke, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGal, Susan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIrvine, Judith T., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLempert, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLempert, Michael, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMeek, Barbra A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNakassis, Constantine V., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPhilips, Susan U., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSilverstein, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSummerson Carr, E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle i